  "prompt": "How do I change gender in booked IRCTC e-tickets?",
  "response": "To change the gender in a booked IRCTC e-ticket, you have a few options:\n\n1. Online Method:\n- Log in to your IRCTC account\n- Go to 'My Transactions'\n- Select the specific ticket\n- Click on 'Modify Passenger Details'\n- Update the gender\n- Save the changes\n\n2. Contact IRCTC Customer Support:\n- Call their helpline\n- Email them with ticket details\n- Request gender modification\n- Provide necessary identification proof\n\n3. At Railway Station Reservation Counter:\n- Visit the reservation counter\n- Carry original ticket and ID proof\n- Request passenger detail modification\n\nImportant Points:\n- Changes can usually be made before chart preparation\n- Some modifications might incur a nominal fee\n- Ensure details match government-issued ID\n- Always carry original ticket and ID proof\n- Changes are subject to IRCTC's terms and conditions\n\nRecommendation: Do this as early as possible to avoid last-minute complications.",
